			<div class="post-text">
				<p>I was playing with a <a href="http://www.jeria.net/?p=7" title="Script for reading CSS properties of a page">neat script</a> that reads CSS properties of a given element, but there&#8217;s a problem. Fetching background color of an element doesn&#8217;t work in Safari, if it was inherited instead of explicitly set in CSS.</p>
<p>Does anyone know how to reliably get that information?</p>
